    <!-- Chosen Palette: Calm Neutrals -->
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The application is designed as a single-page narrative dashboard that guides the user through the strategic analysis in a logical flow. It starts by defining the problem (The 'Red Ocean' of current competitors), presents the core strategic shift (The 'Strategy Canvas' using an interactive chart), details the innovative solution (The 'Blue Ocean' of new features), and concludes with sustainability (The 'Defensive Moat'). This thematic, top-down structure is more intuitive and engaging for a user than a simple text document, transforming a static report into an exploratory experience that builds understanding step-by-step. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: Competitive Disadvantages -> Goal: Compare -> Interactive Cards -> JS updates a central text block to focus user attention on one competitor at a time. ERRC Grid -> Goal: Analyze Change -> Interactive Bar Chart (Chart.js/Canvas) -> Buttons filter the chart data to visually demonstrate the Eliminate-Reduce-Raise-Create framework, making an abstract concept tangible. New Market Features -> Goal: Organize/Inform -> Interactive Grid -> JS reveals details on click, highlighting the core innovations that create the new market. Defensibility -> Goal: Summarize -> Clean Icon-based Layout -> Provides a clear, impactful summary of the business's long-term advantages. All interactions use vanilla JS. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
    <style>
